<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Inverse Kinematics" class="currentChild" href="Inverse_Kinematics">Inverse Kinematics</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
A means of <a title="three-dimensional (3D) animation" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/three-dimensional_%283D%29_animation">three-dimensional (3D) animation</a> which makes use of <a title="Hierarchical Link" href="Hierarchical_Link">hierarchical link</a>s and a feedback mechanism to animate objects. In inverse kinematics, a "child" object (say, a rabbit's ears) will be animated and, due to the feedback mechanism, the "parent" object of that child (say, the rabbit's head) will also move from a certain point. In turn, the parent of the parent (say, the rabbit's body) will also move. 
</p>
